This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald J. Trump on October 29, 2018. The memorandum delegates authority to the Secretary of State, in coordination with other government officials, to submit a certification to Congress as required by section 1244 of the National Defense Authorization Act for Fiscal Year 2019. The memorandum also states that this delegation of authority applies to any future public law that is the same or substantially similar to the referenced provision. The Secretary of State is directed to publish this memorandum in the Federal Register.